OL,3,CDavid Lammy becomes first black Lord
OL,4,CChancellor
OL,6,FDavid Lammy has been sworn in as Lord
OL,7,FChancellor and Secretary of State for
OL,8,FJustice, becoming the first black
OL,9,Fperson to hold the role.
OL,11,FThe deputy prime minister, who was
OL,12,Fpreviously foreign secretary, replaced
OL,13,FShabana Mahmood as justice secretary,
OL,14,Fand was sworn in before the top judges
OL,15,Fin England and Wales, including Lady
OL,16,FChief Justice Baroness Carr.
OL,18,FThe new Solicitor General Ellie Reeves
OL,19,Fwas also sworn in at the ceremony at
OL,20,Fthe Royal Courts of Justice in London.
